.SH NAME
CSS.escape_static \- CSS: escape() static method
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]CSS.escape()\f[B]\f[R] static method returns a string
containing the escaped string passed as parameter, mostly for use as
part of a CSS selector.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
CSS.escape(str)
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]str\f[R]
The string to be escaped.
.SS Return value
The escaped string.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Basic results
.IP
.EX
CSS.escape(\[dq].foo#bar\[dq]); // \[dq]\[rs]\[rs].foo\[rs]\[rs]#bar\[dq]
CSS.escape(\[dq]()[]{}\[dq]); // \[dq]\[rs]\[rs](\[rs]\[rs])\[rs]\[rs][\[rs]\[rs]]\[rs]\[rs]\[rs]{\[rs]\[rs]\[rs]}\[dq]
CSS.escape(\[aq]\-\-a\[aq]); // \[dq]\-\-a\[dq]
CSS.escape(0); // \[dq]\[rs]\[rs]30 \[dq], the Unicode code point of \[aq]0\[aq] is 30
CSS.escape(\[aq]\[rs]0\[aq]); // \[dq]\[rs]ufffd\[dq], the Unicode REPLACEMENT CHARACTER
.EE
.SS In context uses
To escape a string for use as part of a selector, the
\f[CR]escape()\f[R] method can be used:
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] element = document.querySelector(\[ga]#${CSS.escape(id)} > img\[ga]);
.EE
.PP
The \f[CR]escape()\f[R] method can also be used for escaping strings,
although it escapes characters that don\[cq]t strictly need to be
escaped:
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] element = document.querySelector(\[ga]a[href=\[dq]#${CSS.escape(fragment)}\[dq]]\[ga]);
.EE
